“I was in the right place at the
right time,” she said. ,

In 1960, at the age of 22, Nash
found a project in Nashville, Tenn.,
to test nonviolent direct action in
the desegregation of segregated
lunch counters. Nash led several of
her contemporaries in sit-ins at six
eateries with segregated lunch coun-

