No, not physically littl
— Pitt manages to compet
in D-I basketball after all. ..
Financially little.

It’s true: Most people like me
who show up to class and. call
themselves University students
are thousands of times smaller
than many hedge fund manag-
ers and corporate CEOs, that
is, if we’re talking net worth or
annual income.

Surely, being little in this way
allows us to worry less about kid-
nappers trying to squeeze us of

ransom money or distant rela-

tives extending ulterior—motive-
derived kindness. But all too often
our smallness confers unsavory
vulnerability, especially when it

. comes to having to make consum-

er decisions. For example, even a
part-time paycheck from Starbucks
won’t allow a college student to pay
for both tuition and a lawyer to
